correctness.rationale: Multiple schema violations, missing values, and one clear unit error reduce correctness despite some correctly extracted items (PEALD method, DADI/TMGa/DEZ precursors, O2 plasma, TFS200 tool, 250 °C, 38 W plasma power, 1:1:1 supercycle ratio, and 1.26% uniformity; device Vth ≈ -3.5 V and SS ≈ 230 mV/dec). Key issues: (1) Growth-per-cycle unit/value mismatch: article reports ~0.21 nm/cycle, but extraction uses 0.21 Å, off by 10×; should be 2.1 Å or 0.21 nm. (2) reactantSelection.coReactant lists only a single entry with compound "InGaZnO"; per schema and article, O2 plasma is the co-reactant for each sub-oxide and should be provided for InOx, GaOx, and ZnOx separately. (3) Widespread nulls/placeholder strings violate schema and the "no empty/null" rule: pressure, filmThickness (both inside thicknessControl and at processParameters level), numberofCycles, nucleationPeriod, dosingTime/purgeTime/flowRates (empty arrays), conformality.aspectRatio, elementalConcentration.values, roughness.value, filmDensity.value, deviceProperties.fieldEffectMobility and onOffRatio, otherAspects.filmStability/reproducibility booleans set to null, and multiple "Not Found" placeholders (carrierGas, purgingGas, substrate, deliveryMethod, reactor.manufacturer, etc.). These must be populated with valid QUDT units and numbers or omitted if optional; required fields cannot be empty/null. (4) saturation set to false without support in the article. (5) crystallinity set to "amorphous" without explicit evidence in the provided text or a cited method. (6) filmComposition.atomicRatio "1:1:1" is presented without a characterization method and may conflate cycle ratio with measured atomic ratio. (7) coReactant/carrier/purging gases are not evidenced; placeholders are not acceptable. To correct: fix GPC to 0.21 nm (or 2.1 Å); supply per-compound co-reactant entries; either provide measured pressure, film thickness, cycle counts, dosing/purge times, flow rates, aspect ratio, composition/roughness/density with proper units and methods, or restructure to meet schema (no nulls); remove unsupported assertions (saturation=false, amorphous) or justify with source; replace placeholders with actual values (e.g., carrier/purging gas) or omit if schema allows.

completeness.rationale: Several key fields are missing, incorrectly populated, or violate the schema, and multiple ALD processes described in the article are not represented. Specific issues: (1) Supercycle/GPC: Growth-per-cycle is wrong by unit/value (article: ~0.21 nm/cycle; extracted: 0.21 Å/cycle). (2) ProcessParameters: pressure has null quantityValue/quantityKind; substrate, carrierGas, purgingGas, deliveryMethod set to 'Not Found'; nucleationPeriod null; dosingTime, purgeTime, and flowRates are empty arrays; filmThickness and numberofCycles are null. 'Saturation' is set to False without support in the text. (3) MaterialProperties: conformality.aspectRatio is null; filmComposition.elementalConcentration values are null; atomicRatio '1:1:1' is the cycle ratio, not a measured composition; roughness and filmDensity are null; crystallinity 'amorphous' lacks a stated method; opticalProperties/electricalProperties set to None (type/schema mismatch). (4) DeviceProperties: onOffRatio and fieldEffectMobility omitted though ION and IOFF are reported (could at least report IOFF and ION within schema constraints or compute ratio if allowed); threshold voltage and SS are correctly extracted. (5) ReactantSelection: coReactant provided only once for 'InGaZnO' rather than per sub-oxide; carrier/purging gases not provided. (6) Multiple processes: the article also reports PEALD Al2O3 (10 nm at 250 °C) and IZO (20 nm, in situ) depositions; only the IGZO process is captured, so additional process instances should be added. To improve completeness, fix GPC units/value, populate pressure with units, provide substrate, carrier/purging gases, dosing/purge/flow parameters (or remove fields if schema allows), add filmThickness and numberofCycles, provide conformality metric if available, replace the atomic ratio with measured composition (or omit if not measured), and add separate ALD processes for Al2O3 and IZO with their reported thickness and conditions.
